I'd like to make a toast.

438
01:04:03,675 --> 01:04:07,637
As scientists, you know
 that there are always questions.

439
01:04:07,720 --> 01:04:10,682
One question leads to another.

440
01:04:10,765 --> 01:04:13,225
There's an infinity of questions.

441
01:04:13,685 --> 01:04:16,438
It won't surprise you that tonight,

442
01:04:16,521 --> 01:04:18,815
I have yet another question.

443
01:04:19,858 --> 01:04:22,610
What is your true connection
 with the sky?

444
01:04:26,906 --> 01:04:28,408
One at a time!

445
01:04:33,830 --> 01:04:35,540
First things first.

446
01:04:38,292 --> 01:04:39,794
To the sky!

447
01:04:40,294 --> 01:04:42,881
Which nourishes us
 and quenches our thirst.

448
01:04:46,718 --> 01:04:48,595
That's the wisdom of the earth.

449
01:04:54,141 --> 01:04:59,146
-He didn't get it.
 -What does that mean?

450
01:04:59,229 --> 01:05:01,649
-That the sky nourishes us?
 -Yes.

451
01:05:01,733 --> 01:05:03,275
Well...

452
01:05:23,796 --> 01:05:26,508
So you're an exoplanet hunter?

453
01:05:26,591 --> 01:05:29,552
But what does that really mean?

454
01:05:30,010 --> 01:05:32,221
It's like science fiction.

455
01:05:33,556 --> 01:05:35,642
And why do you chase planets?

456
01:05:36,225 --> 01:05:38,603
Why does this matter to us?

457
01:05:41,397 --> 01:05:46,694
Planet hunting resonates
 with the public

458
01:05:47,529 --> 01:05:51,407
because it raises fundamental
 questions about our origins,

459
01:05:51,491 --> 01:05:52,992
about why we are here.

460
01:05:53,075 --> 01:05:56,704
And these questions are connected

461
01:05:57,037 --> 01:05:59,874
to our habitat, our earth,

462
01:06:00,207 --> 01:06:03,503
but also to the existence
 of other similar worlds elsewhere

463
01:06:03,586 --> 01:06:05,547
and maybe of life elsewhere.

464
01:06:05,630 --> 01:06:10,133
So when we explain to people

465
01:06:10,217 --> 01:06:14,263
that we are looking for planets
 and for life elsewhere,

466
01:06:14,347 --> 01:06:17,684
obviously it resonates profoundly.

467
01:06:17,767 --> 01:06:20,436
These are age-old questions

468
01:06:20,520 --> 01:06:24,357
that everyone has wondered about
 at some point or another.

469
01:06:24,440 --> 01:06:28,277
And often, we think about them
 when we look up at the sky.

470
01:06:37,954 --> 01:06:44,084
And that's how it's connected
 to our understanding of the sky.

471
01:06:45,044 --> 01:06:48,006
We feel renewed because

472
01:06:48,255 --> 01:06:52,217
when we watch the sky,
 we forget everything we've learned.

473
01:06:52,677 --> 01:06:56,639
We see the immensity in front of us,

474
01:06:57,306 --> 01:06:59,976
and not just in terms of distance.

475
01:07:00,059 --> 01:07:05,023
Of course, people have trouble
 understanding such huge distances.

476
01:07:06,691 --> 01:07:08,818
But there's also an immensity
 of possibilities.

477
01:07:08,901 --> 01:07:11,446
In the sky, our imagination
 takes flight

478
01:07:11,529 --> 01:07:13,615
and everything is possible.

479
01:07:30,048 --> 01:07:33,009
Everything that opens our minds
 is important

480
01:07:33,092 --> 01:07:35,135
and is a catalyst for our growth.

481
01:07:35,218 --> 01:07:38,097
Historically,
 the sky is the first level.

482
01:07:39,390 --> 01:07:42,560
And then understanding the sky,
 and what's behind the sky,

483
01:07:42,644 --> 01:07:44,020
that's the second level.

484
01:07:45,396 --> 01:07:48,024
For me,
 that's what astrophysics is.

485
01:07:53,029 --> 01:07:56,908
It's the scientific explanation

486
01:07:56,991 --> 01:07:59,744
for the wanderings
 of our imagination

487
01:07:59,827 --> 01:08:02,080
beyond the screen of the sky.

488
01:08:48,751 --> 01:08:51,879
If we want to go to a planet
 that we discover,

489
01:08:52,130 --> 01:08:55,550
which might be
 a hundred light years away,

490
01:08:55,633 --> 01:08:57,760
it will take us 10,000 years
 to get there.

491
01:08:57,844 --> 01:09:00,096
10,000 years to get there.

492
01:09:00,179 --> 01:09:03,391
So we either put people to sleep
 and wake them when they arrive,

493
01:09:03,474 --> 01:09:06,894
and here we're starting
 to get into science fiction,

494
01:09:08,354 --> 01:09:10,815
which I've always loved,
 and I still love.

495
01:09:11,107 --> 01:09:14,026
Or else we create
 something like Noah's ark.

496
01:09:14,110 --> 01:09:16,696
We send out families

